27:01.062 --> 27:02.283
He's saying gems.

27:03.945 --> 27:10.053
And, and, you know, I, when I was 15 years old, 14 years old, I was, I had a paper out.

27:10.093 --> 27:11.094
I delivered the newspaper.

27:11.635 --> 27:12.216
I love this.

27:12.416 --> 27:17.022
It was my way of, you know, because I had to learn what the value of money is.

27:17.062 --> 27:17.623
Yeah.

27:17.643 --> 27:20.306
And so if I use AI today, I mean, I'm,

27:20.546 --> 27:40.562
65 so you know I can maybe be a little lazy with AI but if I was a young person I'd be feeling like I have to learn something but we see a lot of students that they don't care it's like I'm just going to let AI do the work for me and I'm gonna get a good grade and that's not good because our brain is like a muscle and if we don't use it we lose it.

27:42.338 --> 27:55.878
